The sprint table is still referencing to deleted board "rapid_view_id = 2". It's not clear what is the purpose of the RAPID_VIEW_ID in this table.

At an attempt to open a link to an Agile board with an ID that doesn't exist in an instance (either from a saved link or by manually editing the URL in the browser), an error is thrown:
{quote}
Error
rapidViewId
{quote}

Instead, the message should state that the board with given ID doesn't exist or is unavailable.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-11697].
  {panel}

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Install JIRA and JIRA Agile;
# Create the DEMO project;
# Create a scrum board for the DEMO project;
# And rename the user used to create the board (or any board administrator).

h3. Expected Behavior
The user's full name would be displayed in the "Manage Boards" view.

h3. Actual Behavior
JIRA Agile doesn't handle the renamed username, and instead of displaying the user's full name displays 'Anonymous' in the "Manage Boards" screen.
